Reference: SteamGridDB/decky-steamgriddb
-----------------------------------------

The SteamGridDB-maintained Decky Loader plugin
[SteamGridDB/decky-steamgriddb](https://github.com/SteamGridDB/decky-steamgriddb)
is licensed GPL-3.0-or-later. This plugin is **not derived from
that source**: no TypeScript, Python, configuration, or asset files
were copied or transliterated.

What we did learn from reading their open-source code (in
addition to the official SteamGridDB API docs) is purely factual
information — uncopyrightable per idea-expression dichotomy:

- That the SteamGridDB API exposes
  `https://www.steamgriddb.com/api/v2/{grids|heroes|logos|icons}/steam/{steamAppId}`
  as a direct lookup keyed off Steam's app id (i.e. no SGDB-game-id
  resolution required). This is the same shape any client of the
  public API uses; it is documented at the SGDB API homepage.
- That Steam's CEF runtime exposes an `IPC` method
  `SteamClient.Apps.SetCustomArtworkForApp(appId, base64Data,
  format, eAssetType)` that applies custom art instantly without a
  Steam restart, and that `eAssetType` maps as
  `{ Capsule: 0, Hero: 1, Logo: 2, WideCapsule: 3, Icon: 4 }`. This
  is Valve's IPC, not Decky's, but Decky's plugin is the canonical
  reference for the enum values.

We do **not** ship, vendor, or otherwise embed any code, tarball,
or asset from `SteamGridDB/decky-steamgriddb`. We do **not** reuse
their dedicated SteamGridDB API key (the hex-encoded
`deckyloader42069` in their `useSGDB.tsx` is whitelisted server-
side for that plugin only — using it elsewhere would be a TOS
breach). End users of this plugin generate their own SteamGridDB
API key under their own profile.


SteamGridDB API
---------------

This plugin queries `https://www.steamgriddb.com/api/v2/...` at
runtime using the user's own SteamGridDB API key, persisted via
`@steam-loader/plugin-storage` to
`~/.config/steam-loader/plugins/steamgriddb.json` on the user's
machine. The key never leaves the user's device. We do not bundle
or redistribute SteamGridDB's catalogue, thumbnails, or assets;
the UI hotlinks thumbnails directly from the SGDB CDN at view
time, the same way any browser viewing steamgriddb.com does.

SteamGridDB's terms govern the user's use of the API.


Steam CDN thumbnails
--------------------

The library-picker shows each Steam-installed game's default
600×900 capsule by hotlinking
`https://cdn.cloudflare.steamstatic.com/steam/apps/{appid}/library_600x900.jpg`.
Steam's CDN serves these images for use in Steam-related clients;
we do not cache or rehost them.


Steam app manifests
-------------------

The plugin reads `appmanifest_*.acf` files under the user's Steam
library paths to build a `{appid, name}` index of installed
games. These files are owned by the user (Valve writes them, the
user owns the disk); we do not ship them.
